<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1245] C# JSON Protocol uses culture-dependant decimal separator for double</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1245</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;C# JSON protocol uses the current culture to read and write doubles, so the decimal separator is not always a dot. For instance, if the the current culture is fr-FR, a comma is used as decimal separator thus resulting in invalid JSON.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;C#, Windows 7, VS2008&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
